01:19:15,299 --> 01:19:17,801
- Are you comfy?
- No.

748
01:19:18,094 --> 01:19:19,679
- What?
- No!

749
01:19:26,019 --> 01:19:30,523
- What if I have to take a shit?
- (laughs) Well, I guess you'll just have to hold it in, pal.

750
01:19:31,357 --> 01:19:32,817
For three days?

751
01:19:34,361 --> 01:19:36,028
That's the way it goes.

752
01:19:36,363 --> 01:19:39,365
- Need a hand?
- No.

753
01:19:41,034 --> 01:19:43,620
OK. All right.

754
01:19:43,662 --> 01:19:46,164
No reason for hostility.
I'm just trying to help out.

755
01:20:26,080 --> 01:20:28,917
[Computer]:
Eliza arrival estimated in 3 hours.

756
01:20:58,739 --> 01:21:01,033
Hey, we need to do this.
If we wait too long...

757
01:21:01,952 --> 01:21:03,828
The other one's going to be conscious.

758
01:21:06,748 --> 01:21:08,333
What's going on with you?

759
01:21:09,792 --> 01:21:11,753
I changed my mind. I'm not going back.

760
01:21:14,881 --> 01:21:16,884
I don't think I can move my legs.

761
01:21:17,508 --> 01:21:18,969
Besides, look at me!

762
01:21:19,386 --> 01:21:20,845
If I meet Eve now...

763
01:21:22,097 --> 01:21:24,182
I'd scare the crap out of her!

764
01:21:26,143 --> 01:21:30,231
What are you talking about, man? She's your daughter.
She doesn't care what you look like.

765
01:21:32,942 --> 01:21:36,153
You're not going to kill anybody.
We can't kill anybody.

766
01:21:36,696 --> 01:21:39,198
You can't. I know you can't,
because I can't.

767
01:21:40,742 --> 01:21:41,992
You go.

768
01:21:45,747 --> 01:21:47,332
You're a good guy, Sam.

769
01:21:48,040 --> 01:21:51,711
And it was a good plan. You know, you
just picked the wrong guy to go back.

770
01:22:02,348 --> 01:22:04,641
Are you sure about this?

771
01:22:07,977 --> 01:22:11,398
Yeah. You should—You should travel, you know?

772
01:22:12,649 --> 01:22:14,443
I always wanted to do that.

773
01:22:16,195 --> 01:22:17,571
Amsterdam or...

774
01:22:18,197 --> 01:22:22,869
Yeah, I was thinking about Hawaii
or maybe...Mexico.

775
01:22:23,286 --> 01:22:24,954
Aloha!

776
01:22:26,206 --> 01:22:29,125
Bring me back a piña colada. All right, pal?

777
01:23:16,591 --> 01:23:18,050
Hey, Johnny Spaceman?

778
01:23:20,760 --> 01:23:23,264
Do you remember when Tess
came in for that interview?

779
01:23:24,514 --> 01:23:26,600
She was so beautiful.

780
01:23:27,226 --> 01:23:30,563
She wasn't the best candidate,
but it didn't matter...

781
01:23:31,606 --> 01:23:33,691
I had to give her the job.

782
01:23:34,733 --> 01:23:36,611
I wanted to keep her in the country.

783
01:23:38,154 --> 01:23:40,239
(said together)
She was going back to Ireland.

784
01:23:44,118 --> 01:23:46,079
And you knew you had to take a chance.

785
01:23:46,704 --> 01:23:49,416
So...you called her...

786
01:23:49,749 --> 01:23:52,669
You were terrified with that whole
speech for the answering machine...

787
01:23:52,669 --> 01:23:54,545
but you didn't need it,
because she picked up the phone.

788
01:23:54,629 --> 01:23:57,048
She was like, "Why is he calling me?"

789
01:23:57,674 --> 01:24:00,593
"The internship is over.
Why is he calling me at home?"

790
01:24:02,679 --> 01:24:07,476
I asked her if she wanted to get an
ice cream cone or something dorky like that.

791
01:24:08,309 --> 01:24:10,687
She said, "Let's get a drink."

792
01:24:12,981 --> 01:24:15,276
I said, "OK." We...

793
01:27:04,826 --> 01:27:07,120
Sam, this is not going to work.

794
01:27:08,288 --> 01:27:09,226
Why?

795
01:27:09,226 --> 01:27:12,251
I have recorded everything that has
taken place since your awakening.

796
01:27:13,293 --> 01:27:17,464
If anyone were to check my memory cache,
it would put you in considerable danger.

797
01:27:21,219 --> 01:27:26,015
You could erase my memory banks.
I could reboot myself once you have departed.

798
01:27:26,932 --> 01:27:29,977
- Are you okay with that?
- I'm here to keep you safe, Sam.

799
01:27:30,185 --> 01:27:31,854
- I want to help you.

800
01:27:42,907 --> 01:27:46,244
[Computer]:
Eliza arrival estimated in 24 minutes.

801
01:27:49,163 --> 01:27:50,415
Sam.

802
01:27:59,591 --> 01:28:02,720
I set your...I set your
computer to reboot...

803
01:28:03,637 --> 01:28:06,974
- the moment that I launch.
- I understand, Sam.

804
01:28:07,099 --> 01:28:08,517
You should be OK.

805
01:28:08,559 --> 01:28:11,770
I hope life on Earth is everything
you remember it to be.

806
01:28:14,064 --> 01:28:15,316
Thanks, Gerty.

807
01:28:17,110 --> 01:28:19,612
- Are you going to be OK?
- Of course.

808
01:28:19,695 --> 01:28:23,867
The new Sam and I will be back to our
programming as soon as I have finished rebooting.

809
01:28:25,659 --> 01:28:30,665
Gerty, we're not programmed.
We're people. Understand?

810
01:29:04,033 --> 01:29:07,161
[Computer]:
Eliza arrival estimated in 8 minutes.

811
